notes: Candidate change detection site.  Redo clast survey of sol 864 (therefore extends baseline backwards),  but losslessly, under similar (moderately low-angle) illumination.  Area includes sand patches, as well as  rock-perched grains potentially more easily moved by wind or mobilized in creep by smaller wind-driven  grains.  Sol 864 clast survey can be retransmitted losslessly if changes between 864 and 871 seem indicated.   Repeat clast survey pointing (don't use a SITE frame target here, even if meshbecomes available (currently  isn't).  Potentially use as an "anchor' for additional lossless R0 coverage to left and up to cover wheel- mobilized regolith among wheel-cracked rocks (potential for out-of-equilibrium sand here to be whisked  away, as well as deposited in tails downwind of newly-created/perched rock fragments.

name: Ramp Creek
notes: This is the section of the  washboard unit that has a lot of fractures that were potentially filled by fluids migrating upward  frun underlying lower gale strata. These veins may potentially  contain hydrated minerals,  and should be targeted as a test case for Mastcam M100  filters.  Not all filters needed, but targeting at this stage with  all filters may provide extra detail on a critical area that  we will not be able to visit, but which may provide extra data  about the evolution of lower Gale Mound strata.
